value.value: A Niger-Congo language of the Igbo people of southeastern Nigeria.
A Sino-Tibetan language of the Yi people of Southern Sichuan and northern Yunnan provinces of China.
An Eskimo-Aleut language spoken in the northern Northwest Territories and Nunavut Territory of Canada.
An Austronesian language spoken in the Phillipines in northwest Luzon, the Babuyan Islands, Cordillera Administrative Region, Cagayan Valley, parts of Central Luzon, and scattered areas in Mindanao.
An Austronesian language that is a standardized register of Malay and the official language of Indonesia.

The surgical removal of the entire bladder, a portion of the urethra, adjacent lymph nodes, and additional genitourinary structures, including the prostate and a portion of the vas deferens in men, and the ovaries, fallopian tubes, uterus, and a portion of the vagina in women.
A Northeast Caucasian language spoken by the Ingush people in the the Russian republics of Ingushetia and Chechnya.
A group of dialects of the Inuit languages, spoken by the Inupiat people in northern and northwestern Alaska, and part of the Northwest Territories.
An Austronesian language spoken by the Javanese people from the central and eastern parts of the island of Java, Indonesia.
A group of Jewish dialects spoken by the Jews living in Iran.
A continuum of specifically Jewish varieties of Arabic formerly spoken by Arab Jews.
A Turkic language spoken by the Karakalpak people in the Karakalpakstan republic of Uzbekistan.
An Afro-Asiatic Berber language spoken by the Kabyle people in the north and northeast of Algeria.
A Tibeto-Burman language of the Sal branch mainly spoken in the Kachin State of Myanmar and the Yunnan Province of China.
An Eskimo-Aleut language spoken by Greenlandic Inuit in Greenland.
A Niger-Congo Bantu language spoken by the Kamba people of Kenya.
Instillation of a solution into the bladder to provide cleansing or medication.
A Dravidian language spoken predominantly by the Kannada people in India, mainly in the state of Karnataka.
A language from the Dardic subgroup of Indo-Aryan languages spoken primarily in the Kashmir Valley and Chenab Valley of the Jammu and Kashmir state in India.
A Kartvelian language spoken by the Georgian people in Georgia.
A dialect continuum of the Saharan language spoken mainly in Nigeria, Niger, Chad and Cameroon.
A Turkic language that is the official language of the Republic of Kazakhstan.
A Northwest Caucasian language spoken mainly in parts of the North Caucasus republics of Kabardino-Balkaria and Karachay-Cherkessia and in Turkey, Jordan and Syria.
An Austroasiatic language spoken primarily in the Meghalaya state of India by the Khasi people.
An Austroasiatic language that is spoken by the the Khmer people and is the official language of Cambodia.
A Niger-Congo Bantu language spoken primarily by the Kikuyu people of Kenya.
A Niger-Congo language that is the official language of Rwanda.
A Turkic language spoken in Kyrgyzstan, as well as China, Afghanistan, Kazakhstan, Tajikistan, Turkey, Uzbekistan, Pakistan, and Russia.
A Niger-Congo Bantu language spoken by the Ambundu people of Angola.
An Indo-Aryan language belonging to the Indo-European family of languages that is spoken along the western coast of India.
A Uralic macrolanguage spoken by the Komi peoples in the northeastern European part of Russia.
A Niger-Congo Bantu language spoken by the Kongo and Ndundu people living in the tropical forests of the Democratic Republic of the Congo, the Republic of the Congo, and Angola.
An Austroasiatic language spoken on the Kosrae and Caroline Islands of Micronesia, and Nauru.
A Mande language spoken by the Kpelle people of Liberia and Guinea.
A Turkic language spoken by the Karachay and Balkar people in the Kabardino-Balkaria and Karachay-Cherkessia republics of Russia.
A Uralic language spoken mainly in the Russian Republic of Karelia.
A Dravidian language spoken by the Oraon and Kisan tribespeople of  India, Bangladesh, Nepal, and Bhutan.
The surgical removal of all of the prostate as well as some surrounding tissue, including lymph nodes.
A Niger-Congo language that is the national language of Angola and Namibia.
A Turkic language spoken by the Kumyk people of the Dagestan, North Ossetia, and Chechen republics of the Russian Federation.
A continuum of Northwestern Iranian languages spoken by the Kurdish people in Western Asia.
A language isolate that is the native language of the Kutenai people of Montana and Idaho in the United States and British Columbia in Canada.
A Romance language derived from Old Spanish, originally spoken in the former territories of the Ottoman Empire.
A group of north-western Indo-Aryan language varieties spoken in Pakistani Punjab and in parts of the neighboring Azad Kashmir and Khyber Pakhtunkhwa.
A Niger-Congo Bantu language spoken in Zambia and the Democratic Republic of the Congo.
A Kra-Dai language that is the official language of Laos.
An Indo-European Baltic language that is the official language of Latvia.
A Northeast Caucasian language that is spoken mainly by the Lezgin people of Russia.
